msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near02"
msgid "Nice winds today."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near03"
msgid "Rain, rain, go away..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Near04"
msgid "Maybe I'll go to bed."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You really found it?!<2.pa> Ho ho! Incredible!\n"
"After all these years, people still manage\n"
"to surprise me.\n"
"You know, there might be some <3.se_co>treasure<4.re_co>\n"
"that yet sleeps in this ocean. <5.pa>A diligent\n"
"boy like you could get rich finding it...\n"
"May all your delving end in gold!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "talk04"
msgid "Zzz..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>There are tales passed down of sunken\n"
"<2.se_co>treasure <3.re_co>in the ocean around here...\n"
"\n"
"I would look for it myself if I were a bit\n"
"younger, but I've grown old...\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>But you look like you have a young pair\n"
"of legs and a strong back. Do you want\n"
"to go look in my stead?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>How's the treasure hunt going?\n"
"Did you find it yet?<2.pa>\n"
"\n"
"Don't forget, \"<3.se_co>The treasure sleeps in the\n"
"center of the golden triangle<4.re_co>.\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So? Will you look for the sunken <2.se_co>treasure<3.re_co>\n"
"in my place?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I see. Come on back when you change\n"
"your mind."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (long)
#. 6: pause (short)
#. 7: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I couldn't be happier to hear it.<2.pa>\n"
"Now, according to the old tales...\n"
"\n"
"\"<3.se_co>The treasure sleeps in the center of the\n"
"golden triangle<4.re_co>.\"<5.pa>\n"
"\n"
"Oh, by the by, <6.pa>do you happen to have a\n"
"boat?\n"
"\n"
"If not, I can lend you my raft.<7.pa>\n"
"It's tied up at the wharf. Help yourself."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm going to bed now. If you need\n"
"something, please come back tomorrow."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk14"
msgid ""
"<1.so>On rainy days like today, it's best to stay\n"
"away from large bodies of water.\n"
"\n"
"It can be lonely out there.<2.pa>\n"
"Don't do anything reckless."
msgstr ""

